<section class="space-y-4">
<p class="text-2xl font-medium mb-8">Hello,</p>

<p>I'm Shajan Jacob - a software engineer and technical lead based in Kochi, India, with over 8 years of experience designing and building production-grade web applications.</p>

<p>I specialize in backend engineering with <strong>Node.js</strong>, <strong>TypeScript</strong>, and <strong>NestJS</strong>, architecting scalable microservices and real-time systems on <strong>Google Cloud Platform</strong> and <strong>AWS</strong>. My work spans high-throughput APIs, event-driven architectures, and full-stack development - from ideation through deployment and beyond.</p>

<p>Currently, I serve as <strong>Technical Lead at <a href="https://sorice.solutions/" target="_blank" class="link">Sorice Solutions</a></strong>, where I lead architecture decisions, mentor engineers, optimize system performance, and drive end-to-end project delivery. Previously, I was a <strong>Software Engineer at <a href="https://cubettech.com/" target="_blank" class="link">Cubet Techno Labs</a></strong>, where I built APIs, microservices, and serverless solutions, and published the <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/ffmpeg-sdk" target="_blank" class="link">ffmpeg-sdk</a> npm package.

<p>Beyond the keyboard, I'm deeply curious about hardware. The green traces on circuit boards fascinated me as a child, and that curiosity grew into a passion for <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet_of_Things" target="_blank" class="link">IoT</a> and building things with <a href="https://www.raspberrypi.org/" target="_blank" class="link">Raspberry Pi</a>, ESP32, and addressable LEDs. I've built everything from internet-connected Christmas stars to smart AC controllers - blending software with the physical world.</p>

<p>When I'm not coding or tinkering, you'll find me spending time with family, reading a good book, shooting <a class="link" href="/photography/">photographs</a>, or getting lost on the internet learning something new.</p>

<p>I believe great engineering is about people as much as code - whether it's mentoring junior developers, collaborating with cross-functional teams, or building tools that make someone's day a little easier.</p>

<p>I also maintain a <a href="/shelf/" class="link">shelf</a> of books and a <a href="/uses/" class="link">uses</a> page with the tools and gadgets I rely on - take a peek if you're curious.</p>

<p>Want to work together or just say hello? <a href="/contact" class="link">Get in touch</a>.</p>

